<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She is the former model and radio host who always puts on a fashionable display.</p>

<p>And Kelly Brook once again cut a chic figure while arriving to present her Heart FM show at London's Global studios on Tuesday.</p>

<p>The presenter, 40, looked radiant in a lemon yellow ruffled blouse and high waisted jeans as she reported for duty on her drive time radio show.</p>

<p>Fashionista: Kelly Brook once again cut a chic figure while arriving to present her Heart FM show at London 's Global studios on Tuesday</p>

<p>Kelly's pretty shirt featured frills at the shoulder and chest and was tucked into her faded blue jeans.</p>

<p>The beauty boosted her height with a pair of tan heeled sandals, while she carried her essentials in a quilted black handbag.</p>

<p>She swept her brunette locks into a high ponytail for the occasion, while she enhanced her features with a minimal make-up palette. </p>

<p>Kelly was clearly in high spirits as she flashed a warm smile before making her way into the building. </p>

<p>Stylish arrival: The presenter, 40, looked radiant in a lemon yellow ruffled blouse and high waisted jeans as she reported for duty on her drive time radio show</p>

<p>Kelly's stylish display comes as she admitted she's 'not worried' about her 'weight creeping up'.</p>

<p>She also declared 'diets shouldn't be about deprivation', after revealing she shed a whopping two stone in March.</p>

<p>While she has been keeping busy by exercising at home, her diet consists of 'healthy, low-calorie meals' with sweet treats such as popcorn and homemade fruit lollies.</p>

<p>Lovely: Kelly's pretty shirt featured frills at the shoulder and chest and was tucked into her faded blue jeans</p>

<p>The details: The beauty boosted her height with a pair of tan heeled sandals, while she carried her essentials in a quilted black handbag</p>

<p>The brunette beauty has been candid about her weight fluctuating, with the bombshell slimming down to a size 10-12 after going to a size 16.</p>

<p>On her current figure, she told new! magazine: 'I'm a real foodie and enjoy cooking. I wasn't surprised at all to see my weight creep up a little over the last few weeks.</p>

<p>'[I've gained] a few pounds, but I'm not worried. I know I can lean on the SlimFast 3.2.1. Plan to deal with my weight loss ups and downs, so I can get back on track.</p>

<p>'It's easy and it works. Diets shouldn't be about deprivation - they need to be sustainable after all.'</p>

<p>Cheerful: Kelly was clearly in high spirits as she flashed a warm smile before making her way into the building</p>
